1
00:00:06,428 --> 00:00:09,438
Guru Mahārāj said, “Why do we offer
a flower to the book before the class?”

2
00:00:09,438 --> 00:00:11,142
A garland, flower, something.

3
00:00:11,142 --> 00:00:14,156
[Key to Kṛṣṇa]

4
00:00:14,356 --> 00:00:18,291
Acknowledge first of all, it’s the book,
it’s spiritual substance;

5
00:00:18,291 --> 00:00:21,421
it’s a passive, posing
representation as a book,

6
00:00:21,421 --> 00:00:24,223
but actually it’s spiritually
conscious substance

7
00:00:24,223 --> 00:00:27,899
that wants to be distributed.

8
00:00:27,900 --> 00:00:31,037
Kṛṣṇa wants to distribute Himself.

9
00:00:31,037 --> 00:00:34,326
We can offer ourselves as agents

10
00:00:34,326 --> 00:00:36,822
so whenever some opportunity comes,

11
00:00:36,823 --> 00:00:39,889
rather we should jump for that.

12
00:00:39,889 --> 00:00:44,185
When Gurudev had
the big operation in Soquel

13
00:00:44,201 --> 00:00:46,978
and he thought 
he might not survive,

14
00:00:46,978 --> 00:00:48,755
and he came back

15
00:00:48,771 --> 00:00:52,393
—and it was a heart-breaking situation
to see him like that—

16
00:00:52,423 --> 00:00:56,018
and he came back to the Maṭh
because he said,

17
00:00:56,018 --> 00:01:00,753
“I’d rather leave the world
at the Maṭh than in a hospital”,

18
00:01:00,753 --> 00:01:03,865
everybody was very sad, 
emotional.

19
00:01:04,080 --> 00:01:07,756
And then someone wanted
to get initiated,

20
00:01:07,756 --> 00:01:10,219
like, the next day
or something,

21
00:01:10,220 --> 00:01:12,902
and Gurudev, suddenly
his whole mood changed

22
00:01:12,902 --> 00:01:19,346
and he said,
“They still want service from me.”

23
00:01:19,361 --> 00:01:20,816
That’s what he said,

24
00:01:20,832 --> 00:01:22,751
“They’re still accepting 
service from me,

25
00:01:22,751 --> 00:01:25,501
they want to use me in service.”

26
00:01:25,501 --> 00:01:28,100
His whole mood …
Then he was happy,

27
00:01:28,100 --> 00:01:32,258
even with the bag and like,
the whole horrific situation,

28
00:01:32,258 --> 00:01:37,660
he was now feeling
very happy inside

29
00:01:37,660 --> 00:01:40,834
that some service 
had come to him.

30
00:01:40,834 --> 00:01:48,591
So, particularly the service
of reproduction, talking,

31
00:01:48,591 --> 00:01:52,210
what we’ve heard 
from the Guru-varga.

32
00:01:52,748 --> 00:01:59,403
And Saraswatī Ṭhākur said
the only famine he recognises in the world:

33
00:01:59,694 --> 00:02:02,941
Kṛṣṇa-kaṭha durvita;

34
00:02:02,941 --> 00:02:06,300
the only shortage
is talking about Kṛṣṇa.

35
00:02:06,300 --> 00:02:09,739
Just talk about Kṛṣṇa, 
and say Kṛṣṇa,

36
00:02:09,739 --> 00:02:11,787
over and over again 
as much as possible.

37
00:02:11,787 --> 00:02:15,501
If you can’t think of anything else,
just say that.

38
00:02:15,562 --> 00:02:17,942
Guru Mahārāj said 
that Saraswatī Ṭhākur

39
00:02:17,942 --> 00:02:19,895
would sometimes go 
around the press

40
00:02:19,895 --> 00:02:22,380
looking at the articles, 
and suddenly say,

41
00:02:22,380 --> 00:02:24,737
“How many times 
did they say Kṛṣṇa?”

42
00:02:24,737 --> 00:02:28,231
“A lot. It’s a good article.”

43
00:02:29,861 --> 00:02:33,841
Kṛṣṇa, Gaurāṅga, Nityānanda.

44
00:02:34,549 --> 00:02:39,463
When Nimāi Paṇḍit 
commanded Murāri Gupta,

45
00:02:39,463 --> 00:02:41,757
when he appeared at his house
and he opened the door, like,

46
00:02:41,757 --> 00:02:43,164
(knock knock knock knock)

47
00:02:43,164 --> 00:02:45,181
and he opened the door
and he was Varāhadev,

48
00:02:45,181 --> 00:02:48,510
he’s as the Varāha incarnation,

49
00:02:48,510 --> 00:02:51,628
and goes in the room
and picks up the water jug …

50
00:02:52,576 --> 00:02:57,866
“Murāri, say something.
Don’t just stand there, say something.”

51
00:02:57,904 --> 00:03:01,700
And Murāri Gupta says,

52
00:03:03,331 --> 00:03:07,623
“If Ananta Śeṣa
—your other self expansion—

53
00:03:07,623 --> 00:03:14,062
if Ananta Śeṣa, who’s been trying
to glorify you since the begining of time

54
00:03:14,062 --> 00:03:18,181
with his innumerable tongues
and mouths,

55
00:03:18,181 --> 00:03:23,203
is unable to exhaust
even one of your glories,

56
00:03:23,203 --> 00:03:27,047
what can someone like me say?”

57
00:03:27,370 --> 00:03:29,759
But that’s his glorification,

58
00:03:29,759 --> 00:03:34,798
that’s why he’s qualified
by identifying his lack of qualification,

59
00:03:34,798 --> 00:03:39,515
saying, “If you as your expansion
are unable to, what can I say?”

60
00:03:39,537 --> 00:03:41,815
But that’s a śloka.

61
00:03:41,940 --> 00:03:46,070
You can chant that prayer
and be happy,

62
00:03:46,102 --> 00:03:50,687
and find the key
to Kṛṣṇa conception.

63
00:03:50,764 --> 00:03:55,540
Acknowledging 
your own disqualification

64
00:03:55,540 --> 00:03:57,783
but not allowing that
to dissuade you

65
00:03:57,783 --> 00:04:01,947
from trying to praise the Lord
and His devotees.

66
00:04:02,240 --> 00:04:06,240
Hare Kṛṣṇa

